cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.CV, cs.CL, cs.NE 

The paper presents a new algorithm for semi-supervised representation learning, which is a common topic in machine learning and artificial intelligence. The use of Hilber-Schmidt Independence Criterion (HSIC) as the dependence measure suggests that the paper may belong to the sub-category of cs.LG (Machine Learning). The focus on mapping data to a lower-dimensional space and finding a discriminative mapping suggests that the paper may also belong to the sub-categories of cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing). The use of real-world datasets and the mention of non-linear transformations suggest that the paper may also belong to the sub-categories of cs.CV (Computer Vision) and cs.CL (Computation and Language).
